Class TaggedKey

  • java.lang.Object
    • TaggedKey
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<TaggedKey>, org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable, org.apache.hadoop.io.WritableComparable<TaggedKey>

    public class TaggedKey
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.apache.hadoop.io.WritableComparable<TaggedKey>
    TaggedKey is the "key" that we send from the Mapper to the Reducer, thus it has to implement Writable. It also implements Comparable, that gives us the method compareTo() called in the Sorter, this method will give us 3 result : (0 : same tag),(-10 : city with region), and (10 : region with city). It's a "structure" formed with a String that will contain the actual informations: natural key, and an integer as a "tag" to identify if the informations are coming from the CityMapper (set to "10") or from the RegionMapper (set to "0"). -------------------------------------------------------------------------- We could implement Writable only and use the compareTo() of the Sorter, in it we could have done what this compareTo() is doing? -------------------------------------------------------------------------- *

    Naji

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(TaggedKey o)
        compareTo(AnotherTaggedKey) compare the two, by comparing their natural key first and then their "tags". -If the tag is the same result is going to be (0), in other words if those two keys came from the same mapper the result of this method is zero. -If the first one came from CityMapper and the second from RegionMapper the result is going to be (-10) that would put the data with the first TaggedKey last in the set of data. -If the first one came from RegionMapper and the second from CityMapper the result is going to be (10) and that would put the data with the first Taggedkey first in the set of data.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<TaggedKey>
